txt.en:
'Ooh, I am done for. Those thieving shrews have stolen every single bit of my produce, if you can believe it. And those constables and watchers are of no help at all!

'Habbo thinks the shrews took them into that tunnel that just opened up to the south-east. If you... happen to find yourself inside that tunnel and see my vegetables, please bring some of them back!'

<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This quest will be removed from your quest log when the current festival ends.</rgb>
'Splendid! My lovely vegetables! Thank goodness you came along, friend.'
You have rescued a dozen of Corbo's stolen vegetables from the shrew-tunnel beneath Staddle's farmland. You should return them to him at the Staddle village centre in Bree-land.
Thieving shrews have stolen Corbo Tunnelly's vegetables.
Return the vegetables to Corbo Tunnelly
Corbo has asked you to recover some of his vegetables should you happen to find yourself in the shrew-tunnel located south-east of the Staddle village centre in Bree-land.
